StartPoint: Take the Kolab-Terrace road, turning right onto gravel road toward Lava Point.  At the first fork, stay left.  At the next fork, go right, following the sign for the West Rim Trail and MIA camp.  From gate, take road 4.3 miles to where you'll park.  At 1.4 miles from the gate/sign there is a locked gate which requires an NPS 1D1 key.  As you continue, stay right and you will come to a circular pull around.  Park here. Don't try to continue on steep unmaintained ATV trak that drops off ridge to the left.
Directions: Walk along ridge-top trail for approximately 0.43 miles.  You will know you are approaching the reference tree after crossing a downed weathered log without bark .  Coninue for approx 0.25 miles to a forked dead-top ponderosa of approx. 60 cm DBH (tag on back #3895) and 2-3 meters off the right-hand side of the trail.  (Ref treee is at: UTM 0324805, 4137386, NAD 83).  Head downslope through thick oak, manzanita and juniper at an azimuth of 64 deg. for 0.12 miles.  It may be faster to zig-zag through open patches than walking straight down.  Plot is located more or less in the draw.
Comments: Used declination of 13.5 for plot Azimuth.  This plot is somewhat different in composition in that most of the juniper on the plot is Rocky Mountain Juniper (Juniperus scopularum) instead of Utah Juniper.  There is also a large component of Quercus gambelii and a few ponderosas.  This mix seems typical of midslope, northfacing sites on the mesa.
